The paper deals with the capacity of caching networks, which is a topic that falls under the information theory (cs.IT) sub-category. The network involves multiple users communicating over a shared link, which suggests that the paper may also belong to the networking and internet architecture (cs.NI) sub-category. The use of caching and index coding techniques indicates that the paper may also be relevant to the data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) and signal processing (cs.SI) sub-categories. Finally, the paper proposes an achievable scheme that is order-optimal in certain asymptotic regimes, which suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category.
